direction: right

*.style.border-radius: 8
*.style.font-size: 13
*.style.fill: "#f5f5f5"
*.style.stroke: "#333333"

# --- Entry ---

entry: |md
  **/docs-workflow-planning**

  - <ticket>
  - --base-path <path>
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#f5f5f5"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}

# --- Read requirements ---

read-reqs: |md
  **Read Inputs**

  - requirements/requirements.md
  - code-analysis registry.json
    + ONBOARDING.md (optional)
  - pr-analysis PR-*.md (optional)
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#f5f5f5"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}

# --- docs-planner agent ---

docs-planner: |md
  **docs-planner agent**
  LLM subagent

  - gap analysis (existing vs needed)
  - module specs + prerequisites
  - implementation order, assembly
  - scope-gate by onboarding_priority:
    read-first -> full, read-second ->
    summary, skip -> none
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#e8e8e8"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 3
  style.double-border: true
}

# --- Verify ---

verify: |md
  **Verify Plan**

  - check plan.md exists
  - cross-check vs registry.json
  - warn if skip module got
    a full spec
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#f5f5f5"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}

# --- Sidecar ---

sidecar: |md
  **Write Sidecar**

  - count Module: specs in plan
  - module_count field
  - step-result.json
  - orchestrator stops if 0
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#f5f5f5"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}

# --- Flow ---

entry -> read-reqs
read-reqs -> docs-planner: "requirements.md\n+ scope inputs"
docs-planner -> verify: "plan.md"
verify -> sidecar: "module_count"
